        <h3 class="block-title">News &amp; Events</h3>
    
      <h4><a href="http://www.bpl.bc.ca/locations-hours#holiday-closures" title="Holiday closures">Holiday closures</a></h4><p>All branches will be closed Friday, March 25 for Good Friday, and Sunday, March 27 and Monday, March 28 for Easter.</p><h4><a href="http://www.bpl.bc.ca/locations-hours#holiday-closures" title="Holiday and early closures"></a><a href="http://www.bpl.bc.ca/have-you-recently-received-your-canadian-citizenship" title="Cultural Access Pass">Cultural Access Pass</a></h4><p>Are you a new Canadian citizen? Get your Cultural Access Pass and visit more than 600 cultural attractions across Canada, all for free!</p><h4><a title="NewToBC.ca" href="http://newtobc.ca/" style="font-size: 1em;">NewToBC</a></h4><p>NewToBC unites 10 public library systems in Metro Vancouver to help connect newcomers with programs and services in their community.</p><h4><a title="Metrotown transit notice" href="/news/metrotown-transit-notice">Metrotown transit notice</a></h4><p>The elevator at the Metrotown SkyTrain station is out of service until early 2016, due to station upgrades.</p><h4><a href="http://www.bpl.bc.ca/satisfaction-survey" title="Satisfaction Survey for BC Public Education System 2016">Satisfaction Survey for BC Public Education System 2016</a></h4><p>Take the Ministry of Education's annual survey and help identify strengths and areas for improving the student experience in education.</p>  
</section>  <section class="block block-views block-views-we-recommend-block-2 block-even clearfix">

        <h3 class="block-title">We Recommend...</h3>
    
      <div class="view view-we-recommend view-id-we_recommend view-display-id-block_2 view-dom-id-e987741fe46d2756c07c1da377dd8627">
        
  
  
      <div class="view-content">
        <div class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first">
      
          <div><a href="https://burnaby.bibliocommons.com/item/show/1135318002"><img src="http://www.bpl.bc.ca/sites/default/files/styles/we_recommend/public/uploads/materials/images/undesired.jpg?itok=COf1vtpi" width="72" height="111" alt="The Undesired, by  Yrsa Sigurðardóttir" /></a></div>    
          <h4 class="term-link"><a href="https://burnaby.bibliocommons.com/item/show/1135318002">The Undesired</a></h4>    
  <div>        <em>Yrsa Sigurðardóttir</em>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-body">        <div class="field-content"><p>Aldis is working in a juvenile detention centre in rural Iceland. She witnesses something deeply disturbing in the middle of the night; soon afterwards, two of the boys at the centre are dead. Decades later, single father Odinn is looking into alleged abuse at the centre following the unexplained death of the colleague who was previously running the investigation. The more he finds out, though, the more it seems the odd events of the 1970s are linked to the accident that killed his ex-wife. Was her death something more sinister?</p></div>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-edit-node">        <span class="field-content"></span>  </div>  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even views-row-last">
      
          <div><a href="https://burnaby.bibliocommons.com/item/show/981103002"><img src="http://www.bpl.bc.ca/sites/default/files/styles/we_recommend/public/uploads/materials/images/dear-sir-i-intend-to-burn-your-book.jpg?itok=Z9JtQ_jR" width="72" height="125" alt="Dear Sir, I Intend to Burn Your Book: an Anatomy of a Book Burning, by Lawrence Hill" /></a></div>    
          <h4 class="term-link"><a href="https://burnaby.bibliocommons.com/item/show/981103002">Dear Sir, I Intend to Burn Your Book</a></h4>    
  <div>        <em>Lawrence Hill</em>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-body">        <div class="field-content"><p>In this essay, Lawrence Hill shares his response to the people in the Netherlands – descendants of the enslaved in the former Dutch colony of Suriname – who intend to burn his international bestselling book <a title="The Book of Negroes" href="https://burnaby.bibliocommons.com/item/show/728322002">The Book of Negroes</a>.</p></div>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-edit-node">        <span class="field-content"></span>  </div>  </div>
    </div>
  
  
  
      
